Currency Market ‘Freezes’ on Derivative Tax Doubts, Valor Says

-- B y   G a b r i e l l e   C o p p o l a
-- 
2011-07-29T13:29:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/currency-market-freezes-on-derivative-tax-doubts-valor-says.html
Investor uncertainty about how the
Brazilian government will implement a new 1 percent tax on
currency derivative bets is halting transactions in the
country’s currency futures market, Valor Economico  reported ,
citing unnamed sources.  Banks are already passing on the cost of the tax to
clients, increasing costs for all types of operations, including
loans to exporters, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gabrielle Coppola in  Sao Paulo  at 
 gcoppola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Helder Marinho in Sao Paulo at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net  